  "description": [
    "THE BROWNING CHIEF John E Davies Editor and Owner A weekly newspaper published every Friday at Browning Glacier County Montana Entered as 2nd class matter July 15 1931 at the postoffice at Browning Montana under act of March 3 1879 Subscription 200 year in advance PROGRESS IN KOREA Steadfast firmness appears to have won another victory in Korea We have yet to find out exactly what the Communist mean by neutral inspection but this could develop into a big breakthrough on the peace front For effective inspection is the key not only to an armistice in Korea but to proposals for world disarmament The Reds have always before argued that they should do their own inspecting Whatever they chose to report should be accept ed by other nations without ques tionthat was the general atti tude For five years all United Nations efforts to control atomic bombs ran aground on this reef And in Korea it begun to look as if Red rejection of real inspec tion would wreck the truce nego tiations But then as well as on several other occasions when the Communist found the UN posi tion firm they made a concess ion They have left themselves"
  ],
